# Host a Static Website on EC2

How to host a **static HTML/CSS/JS website** on your AWS EC2 instance using **Nginx**.

## Step 1: Install Nginx
**Amazon Linux:**
```powershell

  sudo yum update -y                (update instance)
  sudo yum install nginx -y         (install nginx)

## Step 2: Start and Enable Nginx
  sudo service nginx start          (start nginx)
  sudo service nginx status         (check status)

## Step 3: Upload or Extract Your Website Files
  1)  scp -i "your-key-path.pem" website.zip ec2-user@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:.    (upload project)
  2)  Navigate to website folder and unzip:

      cd /usr/share/nginx/html       (default Nginx directory)
      sudo rm index.html             (remove default file)
      sudo unzip ~/website.zip       (unzip project files)
      sudo chown -R nginx:nginx *    (set permissions -Amazon Linux)

## Step 4: Check Security Group
Ensure HTTP (Port 80) is allowed in your EC2 Security Group. 

## Step 6: Access Your Website
http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

âš¡ Quick Tips
Restart Nginx after changes:
  sudo service nginx restart 
